  "grammar_point": {
    "title": "Possessives with 的 (de)",
    "explanation": "的 (de) is placed between a pronoun/name and a noun to show possession, like 's in English. 我的 = my, 你的 = your, 他的 = his, 她的 = her. You can also use names: 小明的狗 = Xiao Ming's dog.",
